      <p class="tbl-note">*Based on standard 3mg melatonin gummies. Always check your specific product's Supplement Facts label for the exact milligrams per gummy.</p>
    </div>

    <!-- HOW TO CALCULATE YOUR DOSE -->
    <h2>How to Calculate Your Ideal Melatonin Gummy Dose</h2>

    <p>Finding your optimal melatonin dose requires a systematic approach rather than guessing. The following step-by-step process is the method recommended by sleep specialists at the Cleveland Clinic and the Mayo Clinic. It takes approximately 2-3 weeks but ensures you find the minimum effective dose — which produces the best sleep outcomes with the fewest side effects.</p>

    <div class="num-steps">
      <div class="num-step">
        <span class="num-step-n">1</span>
        <div>
          <h3>Check Your Gummy's Dose Per Serving</h3>
          <p>Flip the bottle and read the Supplement Facts panel. Note the melatonin content per gummy (not per serving — some brands define a "serving" as 2 gummies). Common doses: Olly Sleep = 3mg per gummy, Natrol = 5mg per gummy, ZzzQuil Pure Zzzs = 1mg per gummy, Nature Made = 3mg per gummy. This single number determines how many gummies you should take.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="num-step">
        <span class="num-step-n">2</span>
        <div>
          <h3>Start With the Lowest Dose Possible</h3>
          <p>For most adults, this means one gummy of a low-dose product (1-3mg total). If your gummies are 5mg each, consider cutting one in half to start at 2.5mg. The goal is to find the minimum effective dose. MIT's research on melatonin dosing found that 0.3mg was optimal for many adults — meaning your starting dose is already likely higher than what the science shows is necessary.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="num-step">
        <span class="num-step-n">3</span>
        <div>
          <h3>Test for 5 Consecutive Nights</h3>
          <p>Melatonin's circadian effects build over consistent use. A single night is not a fair trial. Take the same dose at the same time (30-60 minutes before bed) for 5 consecutive nights. Track your sleep onset time, number of awakenings, and how you feel upon waking. A sleep diary or app like Sleep Cycle makes this easier.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="num-step">
        <span class="num-step-n">4</span>
        <div>
          <h3>Evaluate and Adjust</h3>
          <p>After 5 nights, assess: Are you falling asleep faster? Waking up less? Feeling rested in the morning without grogginess? If yes — you have found your dose. If no improvement, increase by one additional gummy (or half a gummy if they are 5mg+). If you are experiencing morning grogginess, reduce the dose. Never exceed 5mg without consulting your healthcare provider.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="num-step">
        <span class="num-step-n">5</span>
        <div>
          <h3>Lock In Your Minimum Effective Dose</h3>
          <p>Once you find the dose that improves your sleep without morning side effects, maintain that dose consistently. Do not increase further "just in case." More melatonin does not mean deeper sleep — it means more side effects. Review your dose with your doctor at your next annual check-up, and consider trying a lower dose after 3 months to see if you still need the full amount.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="tip-box">
      <strong>Pro tip — keep a sleep log:</strong> Track your bedtime, the number of melatonin gummies you took, how long it took to fall asleep, number of awakenings, and your morning alertness rating (1-10). After 2 weeks, patterns will emerge clearly. This data is also invaluable if you need to discuss your sleep with a healthcare provider.
    </div>

    <!-- DOSAGE BY BRAND -->
    <h2>How Many Gummies to Take by Brand</h2>

    <p>One of the biggest sources of confusion is that different melatonin gummy brands contain vastly different doses per gummy. Taking "2 gummies" of Olly Sleep delivers 6mg of melatonin, while taking "2 gummies" of ZzzQuil Pure Zzzs delivers only 2mg — a 3x difference. The table below shows exactly how many gummies to take for the most popular brands to reach common dosage targets. For detailed reviews of each product, see our <a href="/best-melatonin-gummies/">best melatonin gummies</a> ranking.</p>

    <div class="tbl-wrap">
      <table>
        <thead>
          <tr>
            <th>Brand</th>
            <th>Melatonin Per Gummy</th>
            <th>For 1-2mg Dose</th>
            <th>For 3mg Dose</th>
            <th>For 5mg Dose</th>
